text: Hey there team. In prep for today’s big meeting, I wanted to try to set some thoughts for how we should handle whatever the official version of this announcement is
While I know there’s going to be a million questions that come out of it, I’d like (as much for me as anybody) to not be reactionary to whatever they end up announcing.
Let’s stick to the facts and the basic premise that we will need to evaluate these changes/announcements with our full team
Yes, ask questions in the moment - but I want us to collectively steer pretty far from sounding frustrated today.

We’ll get through the meeting and will have a much better sense of what to do thereafter. But I think it’s important enough to warrant this dumb channel just to say let’s be pretty pro with this announcement meeting today. We always are, though I myself have not been super keen on how they’ve opted to roll this out. Going to bury that feeling today and figure out a path internally thereafter.
Let me know any thoughts/questions/concerns. And thanks for being such a great team.

Hello iamewald. Glad you put this up and 100% agree with what you have said. Goes along with what I was thinking, it’s more important to have time, internal alignment and then informed and thoughtful conversations with the right people at adidas.
And I know me typing this makes it a bigger deal than it probably needs to be. Just wanted to make sure we keep it all on the positive and/or we’ll get back to you later type of thoughts.
Keep it on the positive, I tick that.
